4. How the quiz flow works (client-side)


index.html — marketing/landing page, links to quiz.html.
quiz.html loads js/data.js (question + archetype data) and
js/quiz.js. The Quiz class mounts into #quizMount and renders each
of the 15 questions in place — the page comment confirms this is done
without page reloads (a small client-side single-page flow inside a
static HTML file, not React).
On completion, the quiz presumably tallies per-archetype scores and
redirects to results.html with the result encoded somehow (URL params
or localStorage are the two idiomatic options for a vanilla-JS static
site — not confirmed, check js/quiz.js).
results.html loads js/data.js, js/api.js, and js/results.js.
The ResultsPage class:

Renders a hero section with the user's matched archetype
(#resultHero).
Renders a full score breakdown (#scoreChart).
Renders a searchable grid of live facts for all six archetypes
(#factsGrid), sourced from the API Ninjas Animals API via
js/api.js. The search box (#factsSearch) filters client-side —
the page explicitly notes this happens "in your browser — no extra
requests," so all six animals' data is fetched once and cached in
memory.






