To view the static quiz pages (index.html, quiz.html, etc.), you
don't need Next.js at all — serve the repo root with any static server
(e.g. npx serve .) and open index.html, since those pages use relative
paths (css/style.css, js/data.js) and CDN-hosted Bootstrap.

Environment variables (expected, unverified):
Because @neondatabase/serverless is a dependency, a Neon connection
string is almost certainly required for the Next.js side to run against a
real database, conventionally:

DATABASE_URL=postgres://...

Check lib/ for the exact variable name(s) it reads before assuming this.
If the results/leaderboard feature also calls API Ninjas server-side rather
than client-side, an API key env var may be needed too — but as observed,
js/api.js appears to call the Animals API directly from the browser, so
that key (if any) is currently client-exposed. Worth confirming and, if
true, worth moving behind a Next.js API route to avoid leaking the key.


